Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{10-15%minutes}. Cover with a lid to bring to a boil more quickly. Reserve 1 cup potato cooking liquid (1 1⁄2 cups for 4), then drain. Return potatoes to pot and cover to keep warm.

While potatoes cook, wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Peel @garlic{3%cloves}; mince or grate one clove (two cloves for 4 servings; leave remaining garlic whole).

Toss Brussels sprouts on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{5%teaspoon}, a big pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Place whole garlic cloves in the center of a piece of @aluminum foil{}; drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper. Close foil to create a packet and place on one corner of baking sheet.

Roast on top rack until Brussels sprouts are golden brown and tender and garlic is soft, ~{18-22%minutes}.

Pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season generously all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer beef to a #plate{}. Wipe out any burned bits from pan.

> Swap in chicken or pork for beef. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side,
or cook pork to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add minced garlic and @dried thyme{1%tsp} (1⁄2 tsp for 4 servings); cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Remove pan from heat; stir in @water{1/4%cup} (1⁄3 cup for 4), @sherry vinegar{2%tsp} (4 tsp for 4), @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and @cherry jam{1}; scrape up any browned bits, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. If sauce doesn't thicken, return pan to medium-low heat.

Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4). Season with salt and pepper. Add beef and its juices to pan; turn a few times to coat. Transfer beef to a #cutting board{}; tent with foil to keep warm.

Remove roasted garlic from foil and add to pot with potatoes along with @dried thyme{1/4%tsp} (1⁄2 tsp for 4 servings). Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Stir in @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and @butter{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4). Season with salt and pepper.

Slice beef crosswise.

Divide beef, Brussels sprouts, and mashed potatoes between plates. Spoon remaining pan sauce over beef. Serve.